  "text": "To study the role of Rac GTPases in CGNs, we examined mRNA expression of Rac1 (widely expressed) and Rac3 (neuron specific) in the cerebellum using in situ hybridization. At P6, which is when CGNs begin to migrate radially to form the IGL [CITATION_1] , Rac1 and Rac3 mRNAs were expressed almost exclusively in the EGL (Fig. 1A) , where almost all cells are CGNs. At P21, patterns of Rac1 and Rac3 expression became PC dominant, particularly those of Rac3 (Fig. 1B) . Slender cells in the molecular layer (ML), which are implicated in the radial migration of CGNs, were Rac1 positive (Fig. S1A ). Although a previous study reported an absence of Rac3 expression in the cerebellum [CITATION_2] , our results suggested that both Rac1 and Rac3 are expressed in the developing CGNs and that Rac1 expression is more dominant than that of Rac3 (Fig. S1B ).",
